Function Documentation

bool addFlux (  ATOFluxType *  flux  ) 
 

adds a flux to the global flux list.

the fluxname variable of flux is modified if it conflicts with an existing flux that it cannot be merged with. if has found a matching flux then the fluxname will also be changed to the name of the matching flux. if flux does not match nor conflict with any existing global fluxes then the fluxname is not modified. in all cases, though, flux->oldfluxname will save a copy of the fluxname before it is modified to the new flux name. this makes it easy to associate a flux local to a dataset with a global flux (you can thing of fluxname as being globalfluxname, whereas oldfluxname is localfluxname). returns true if the flux name was changed, thus implying that the flux was merged or had conflicted with an existing flux name. if addFlux returns false it does not mean it failed, it just means that your flux name was not changed.

bool convertToPolar (  float &  x,
float &  y
) 
 

take x,y cartesian points and convert to radius and angle (polar).

x will contain the radius, and y will contain the angle in degrees returns false if something went wrong

bool convertFromPolar (  float &  radius,
float &  angle
) 
 

take radius and angle and convert to x,y cartesian points.

radius will contain the x coordinate and angle will contain the y coordinate when the function completes. returns false if something went wrong

void merge (  int  list1num,
float *  list1values,
int  list2num,
float *  list2values,
int &  num,
float *  values
) 
 

merge to lists (assumed sorted).

items that ie, 1 3 5 6 7 merged with 1 2 3 4 5 8 9 becomes 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9

the result size of the list will be stored in num. the result values will be stored in values. it is the callers responsibility to allocate enough spaces in values to store the merge (that means at max, values will need to be allocated to list1num + list2num).
